00:45:15.640 --> 00:45:19.591
But one of the thin film
replacements, well amorphic

00:45:19.591 --> 00:45:21.340
silicon-- you think
you guys know that is,

00:45:21.340 --> 00:45:23.380
but that's deposited silicon.

00:45:23.380 --> 00:45:27.110
It has no real like lattice
structure to speak of.

00:45:27.110 --> 00:45:29.029
It's kind of a disordered
mess, which means

00:45:29.029 --> 00:45:30.320
it has a lot of dangling bonds.

00:45:30.320 --> 00:45:36.430
It has very, very low
lifetimes as a result,

00:45:36.430 --> 00:45:39.680
and also in [INAUDIBLE]
low mobilities.

00:45:39.680 --> 00:45:42.450
You also deposit it and
you deposit with hydrogen

00:45:42.450 --> 00:45:46.261
to passivate all of
those dangling bonds,

00:45:46.261 --> 00:45:48.760
and that's usually done with
either plasma-enhanced chemical

00:45:48.760 --> 00:45:51.990
vapor deposition, and it's
done on either metal or glass.

00:45:51.990 --> 00:45:56.120
And so it has the
potential to be very cheap.

00:45:56.120 --> 00:45:58.300
And then one of
things I think was

00:45:58.300 --> 00:46:01.570
