00:47:19.410 --> 00:47:22.260
actually, because I think
within a very, very short period

00:47:22.260 --> 00:47:24.300
of time, they were able
to get efficiencies

00:47:24.300 --> 00:47:28.240
around 9.6%, which for
a fledgling material

00:47:28.240 --> 00:47:31.610
is incredible, and
I'll get to why that

00:47:31.610 --> 00:47:33.987
was so incredible in a second.

00:47:33.987 --> 00:47:36.320
But again, when thinking about
Earth-abundant materials,

00:47:36.320 --> 00:47:38.153
I really recommend you
guys read this paper.

00:47:38.153 --> 00:47:40.200
This is a paper by Cyrus Wadia.

00:47:40.200 --> 00:47:42.220
It's "Environmental
Science and Technology"

00:47:42.220 --> 00:47:44.261
and it looks all of these
different semiconductor

00:47:44.261 --> 00:47:46.300
